<h2>The Fox and the Grapes</h2>
<p>A hungry fox jumps to reach a farmer's grapes but fails and goes home thinking they are sour. The moral is that nothing comes easy and you shouldn't hate what you can't have. </p>
<h2>The Hare and the Tortoise</h2>
<p>A hare shows off how fast he can run and laughs at a tortoise for being slow. The tortoise challenges the hare to a race, and the hare accepts. </p>
<h2>The Ant and the Dove</h2>
<p>An ant falls into a river and is carried away by the strong current. A dove watching from a nearby tree feels sad for the ant. 
Some other well-known moral stories for children include: The Boy Who Cried Wolf, The Golden Axe, The Proud Rose, The Milkmaid and Her Pail, and The Golden Egg. 
A short story is a brief fictional prose narrative that is usually shorter than a novel and focuses on a single effect or event. Short stories are usually between five and sixty pages long and can be read in a single sitting.</p> 
